  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0af63463b56e7e145bed05d806710549, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FrameManager
  frameText: {fileID: 0}
  playerText:
  - "I\u2026 don\u2019t want to forget... "
  - "I don\u2019t want to forget about her. She is important. So important. Why can\u2019t
    I remember her name?"
  - "What were we doing?\\nWhy is this important again?  I remember\u2026"
  - "What were we doing?\\nWhy is this important again?  I remember\u2026"
  - "Oh\u2026 yes. That's what it was. It started off fine enough. "
  - "Ah\u2026 Yea. She wanted to talk\u2026. "
  - "I.. don\u2019t want to remember anymore."
  - "I.. don\u2019t want to remember anymore."
  - 'She sighed. She seemed unsurprised at my reaction. '
  - "Maybe I shouldn\u2019t remember how it went..."
  - "Maybe I shouldn\u2019t remember how it went..."
  - "Maybe I shouldn\u2019t remember how it went..."
  - "Ah\u2026how could I have forgotten that? It was the last thing I wanted to hear."
  - "Ah\u2026how could I have forgotten that? It was the last thing I wanted to hear."
  - "No, no, no fuck. I don\u2019t want to lose her. I don't want to forget. I must
    have said something. Why can\u2019t I remember properly?"
  - "I can\u2019t. It can\u2019t go this way"
  - "Here it comes\u2026."
  - No. No.
  - "That\u2019s\u2026That\u2019s not it\u2026"
  - That's not what happened.
  - "I\u2026 I broke up with her. She was perfect. But I\u2026"
  - "But I\u2026I was wrong. I mean\u2026how did she react again?"
  - "No\u2026.. No, no, no. "
  - "She\u2019s dead. And it's my fault."
  - "What was her name again\u2026?"
  avoidantText:
  - The sushi place. A common place for you two to be. She liked it, you liked it
    well enough. A good enough place as any for a conversation.
  - She ordered her usual without even looking at the menu. You knew she wanted to
    talk about something. You feared the worst but hoped for the best. Maybe she
    wanted to tell you she wanted to take the next step with you. That would be nice.
  - "You changed the subject. Or tried to. Maybe she would forget about it, or it
    wasn\u2019t that big of a deal.  But then\u2026"
  - I remember. You must remember.
  - "She said, \u201CYou never want to address anything.\u201D You wished you were
    having any conversation but this one. Isn\u2019t it easier to just move on? "
  - "She said, \u201CI don\u2019t know if this is working anymore.\u201D"
  - "Can we not do this now? Is she really doing this now? She started to look like
    there were tears in her eyes. You could feel the heat behind your eyes start
    to build. You didn\u2019t want to cry. "
  - "She said, \u201CYou never listen to me. We have so many problems. I think we
    should break up.\u201D"
  - "I thought it would be better to break up with her first. Then I wouldn\u2019t
    be broken up with."
  - "She immediately broke down in tears. You turned your head away because you didn\u2019t
    want to see her cry. She stood up quickly and ran for the door. "
  - You waited a few minutes. And walked after her. You found her outside, on the
    ground.
  - Naomi
  - ARE YOU SURE?
  - IS THAT REALLY HOW IT WENT?
  - IS THAT REALLY HER NAME?
  - "WHY DON\u2019T YOU REMEMBER?"
  joyfulText:
  - "Your favorite restaurant! Of course. You were on a date with her. She loves
    this restaurant too, that\u2019s why you picked it. Italian. Italian is classic.
    That\u2019s why you went with it. You love Italian. And you wanted to split a
    bottle of wine."
  - She was so excited! And happy! She picked through her plate in front of her.
    Not quite eating full bites. And drinking rather quickly. She must have really
    enjoyed her drink!
  - "She was just nervous because it was such big news. You asked her what she was
    so excited about. But then\u2026"
  - I remember. You must remember.
  - "She said, \u201CYou never take things seriously.\u201D You know she always likes
    your jokes and that you make her laugh. You don\u2019t see what the big deal
    is."
  - "She said, \u201CI don\u2019t know if this is working anymore.\u201D"
  - What about the good times we have had? You have a good thing with her, and you
    think we can get back to that. Why is she ignoring that?
  - "She said, \"You're a great person, but I think I am not good enough for you.
    I think we should break up.\u201D "
  - I thought I could do better.
  - "She smiled tearfully. She knew this would happen. But then she couldn\u2019t
    hold back her tears anymore and got up. She ran for the door."
  - You followed her outside. She looked to her left, but that wasn't the right direction.
    The car came from the right and hit her.
  - Anna
  - ARE YOU SURE?
  - IS THAT REALLY HOW IT WENT?
  - IS THAT REALLY HER NAME?
  - "WHY DON\u2019T YOU REMEMBER?"
  insecureText:
  - Her favorite restaurant. Spanish tapas. She likes it because of the time she
    spent studying abroad in Spain. You always resented her for leaving. She probably
    cheated on you. But it was worth it to be with her. She glowed when she was happy.
  - She ordered her favorite. It probably reminded her of the guy she cheated with.
    She offered some to you, but the thought turned your stomach. Instead, you focused
    on the plate in front of you, picking at it. She smiled at you, but somehow it
    looked sad.
  - "She looked at you knowingly. She knew what you were thinking. She always knew
    that you were worried about some ex or another. You tensed up, holding your glass
    too tightly. She opened her mouth to speak, and then closed it\u2026"
  - I remember. You must remember.
  - "She said, \u201CYou always overthink everything I do.\u201D But she always gives
    you mixed signals! How can you not read into that?"
  - "She said, \u201CI don\u2019t know if this is working anymore.\u201D"
  - Was it something I said? Was it something I did? You can tell she is upset. Should
    you apologize? Or should she apologize?
  - "She said, \u201CI am just not happy. Not anymore. I think we should break up.\u201D"
  - I thought she deserved better. Better than someone as awful as me.
  - She started crying. Ugly. Large fat tears. Your fault. All your fault. She ran
    for the door.
  - ' You sat. You tried to eat a few more bites of your food. It tasted salty from
    the tears that ran down your face. You heard a large commotion and went outside.
    There she was, on the ground.'
  - Maria
  - ARE YOU SURE?
  - IS THAT REALLY HOW IT WENT?
  - IS THAT REALLY HER NAME?
  - WHY DON'T YOU REMEMBER?
